node.text: We spent a week traveling around Northern British Columbia capturing beautiful untamed wilderness! When words and photos fail to do a place justice, video helps to tell the story but there’s nothing like experiencing this in person! #exploreBC  Partner

node.accessibility_caption: Photo by Callum Snape in Bachalpsee with @myswitzerland, @grindelwald_eiger, @jungfrauregion, and @madeinbern. May be an image of nature.

node.text:
We hiked by moonlight for an hour until the first sign of dawn started to light up the sky and we arrived at Lake Bachalp, a small reservoir tucked into the mountainside with one of the most breathtaking views in the entire country!

@jungfrauregion #inLOVEwithSWITZERLAND #jungfrauregion @myswitzerland | Partner

node.accessibility_caption: Photo by Callum Snape in Knight Inlet, British Columbia with @seawolfadventures. May be an image of animal and nature.

node.text:
The Great Bear Rainforest is one of the most special places in the world, but how do you do this place justice? How do you put it into words, into photographs?

I’ll be sharing how I overcome this problem time and time again in a new copy of the Adventure Passport this Sunday. Let me send a copy to your inbox by clicking the link in my bio. Don’t let anxiety and overwhelm get the better of your creativity!

node.accessibility_caption: Photo shared by Callum Snape on August 04, 2021 tagging @newfoundlandlabrador, and @fogoislandinn. May be an image of sky and nature.

node.text:
Tell me somewhere you want to go back to and why?

I’ll go first! Newfoundland, because I’m fascinated with the landscapes there. I think there’s a lot of potential for amazing photographs and stories, the locals are so welcoming and… Icebergs!

node.text:
From traversing glaciers on the Jungfrau to learning how to make Alp Cheese in Gstaad, every moment we spent in @madeinbern was incredible! The excitement of not knowing what was around the next corner made our time here so special!
@myswitzerland #inLOVEwithSWITZERLAND #madeinbern | partner

node.accessibility_caption: Photo by Callum Snape in Coast Mountains. May be an image of nature and sky.

node.text:
Do I hate being alone in the middle of the night in the mountains? Absolutely! Do I think every tiny sound is a bear? 100%! Anyone else relate?

I like to scout my composition the evening before and know exactly what I’m going to shoot so I can drag myself out of my sleeping bag and get back in there as soon as possible! Settings for anyone curious:
Canon 5DMKIV + 16-35L
F/2.8 | 30 Seconds | 35mm | ISO 4000

node.text:
From Montreux to Lausanne and down to Geneva, the scenery in @myvaud is straight out of a fairytale! We spent the day exploring Chillon Castle, walking through vineyards, paddle boarding and we couldn’t resist going for a swim!
@myswitzerland #inLOVEwithSWITZERLAND #MyVaud | Parter

node.text: After a year of not traveling internationally I’ve built up a long list of new countries I want to visit. I’m redeeming my @aeroplan points for some amazing trips over the next year, starting with a much needed vacation in the Caribbean! Aeroplan and @amexcanada have an amazing offer for new Cardmembers. From now until Aug 3rd earn up to 75,000 points with the Aeroplan Card or up to 150,000 points for the Aeroplan Reserve Card. The perks and benefits of these cards have made my trips special from the start, right through to returning home. #MadeForThis | Partner

node.text: I think it’s been a few years since I’ve shared a photo that I took on my phone here on Instagram. Probably because my ego tells me that using a ‘real camera’ is the only way. I really just wanted to take in this moment on my trip with @seawolfadventures and not race around frantically trying to take photos.

node.accessibility_caption: Photo shared by Callum Snape on July 11, 2021 tagging @seawolfadventures. May be an image of nature.

node.text: A moment I’ll never be able to put into words accurately. It was such a privilege to spend a few days with @seawolfadventures to see these beautiful creatures and learn about the indigenous history here! Momma Griz and baby Griz swam out to this little island to feast on shellfish and take a nap in the midday heat 🐻

node.text: When I’m out in nature, I think I’m mostly driven by curiosity and wanting to learn more. It feels like I become hyper aware of every scent, every ripple in the lake, every plant and colour. My brain soaks it all in and somehow helps me turn that into creativity to make a photo.
